<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shandong Secretary on Cooperation with Hong Kong, Macao </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  SK2303124594 Jinan Shandong People's Radio Network in 
Mandarin 2300 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2303124594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jinan Shandong People's Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Mandarin </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The provincial party committee and government 
recently invited some deputies to the second session of the 
eighth National People's Congress and some members to the second 
session of the eighth National Committee of the Chinese People's 
Political Consultative Conference [CPPCC], who were from Hong 
Kong and Macao, to the Taishan Hotel in Beijing to a sincere 
discussion meeting to introduce Shandong's economic and social 
development, investment climate, and policies on bringing in 
investment and to hear the views and suggestions of the friends 
from Hong Kong and Macao on ways for Shandong to further 
accelerate reform and opening up. 
  In his speech, Jiang Chunyun, member of the Political Bureau 
of the CPC Central Committee and secretary of the Shandong 
provincial party committee, expressed heartfelt gratitude, on 
behalf of the provincial party committee and government, to the 
friends from Hong Kong and Macao for their many years of great 
support to the promotion of the economies of Hong Kong, Macao, 
and Shandong and to Shandong's modernization drive. He said: 
Over the past decade and more since reform and opening up 
started, Shandong has continuously emancipated the mind, 
deepened reform, opened wider to the outside world, and 
accelerated development thanks to the guidance of Deng 
Xiaoping's theory of building socialism with Chinese 
characteristics and the CPC's basic line, principles, and 
policies. It has created an excellent situation characterized 
by rapid economic development and social stability and unity. 
Meanwhile, we have remained clear- headed to note that Shandong 
is still lagging rather far behind the requirements of the party 
Central Committee and other provinces and municipalities in 
southern China in its extent of opening up and pace of 
development. It is hoped that friends from Hong Kong and Macao 
will continue their concern and support for Shandong and offer 
more valuable opinions on Shandong's future work. 
  Zhao Zhihao, deputy secretary of the provincial party 
committee and governor of Shandong, introduced to the friends 
from Hong Kong and Macao the basic situation of Shandong, its 
economic and social development in the past few years, its ideas 
for the development and work for some time to come, and the key 
areas of foreign investment for the near future and relevant 
policies. He said: Introducing more investment from abroad is 
the focus of Shandong's endeavor to open to the outside world 
more rapidly. To introduce investment from abroad more rapidly, 
we will greatly optimize the investment climate, simplify work 
procedures, improve the later-stage management of 
foreign-invested enterprises, and provide good-quality and 
high-efficient service to the foreign firms who have come to 
invest in Shandong. 
  He emphasized: We wholeheartedly welcome the friends and 
relatives from Hong Kong and Macao to come to Shandong more 
often to visit, inspect, and give guidance and wholeheartedly 
hoped that, in the future, they will, as always, show concern 
for and support Shandong's modernization drive and, together 
with us, open up a still better future in the economic and trade 
cooperation between Shandong Province and Hong Kong and Macao. 
  Thirty-seven deputies and members attended the meeting, 
including Henry Fok Ying-tung, vice chairman of the National 
CPPCC Committee and president of the China Chamber of Commerce 
of Hong Kong. In their speeches, they held unanimously: 
Shandong is an important coastal open province, which has 
abundant resources and preferential policies for opening up, and 
whose people are loyal to friends and as good as their word. 
They said that they would visit Shandong more often to learn 
more about it and develop economic and trade cooperation. They 
believed that Shandong's economic and trade cooperation and 
exchanges with Hong Kong and Macao would be further developed. 
  Li Zhen, chairman of the provincial people's congress 
standing committee; Lu Maozeng, chairman of the provincial CPPCC 
committee; Song Fatang, standing committee member of the 
provincial party committee and vice governor of Shandong; and 
persons in charge from pertinent provincial departments, were 
present at the meeting. 

</TEXT>

