<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Expands Foreign Economic Cooperation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2403072694 Beijing XINHUA in English 0650 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2403072694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, March 24 (XINHUA) -- This, China's largest 
economic center is broadening ways for foreign co-operation. 
  "The municipal government has published its first batch of 
ten urban infrastructure facilities open to foreign investment 
this year," a municipal official said. 
  Included are 180 projects, each of which is scheduled to use 
at least 10 million U.S. dollars. 
  The city plans to publish a second batch of ten 
infrastructure facilities, including a power plant, a subway, a 
railway, an airport, roads and bridges this year. 
  In addition, it will list large industrial projects for 
foreign co-operation. These projects involve mainly 
petrochemicals, metallurgy, complete sets of power plants, 
telecommunications, electronics, tyres and computers. 
  Foreign business people are welcome to invest in leasing or 
transforming shanghai's urban districts, the official said. 
  According to the official, Shanghai approved the 
establishment of 3,650 foreign-funded projects involving a total 
contractual investment of 7.01 billion U.S. dollars last year. 
  The municipal government has pledged to absorb more foreign 
investment this year than last year. 
  According to statistics, Shanghai has used a total of 14.9 
billion U.S. dollars in foreign investment and approved the 
establishment of 7,500 projects so far. 

</TEXT>

