<F P=100> REGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Uses Auditing in Macrocontrol of Economy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2303094394 Beijing XINHUA in English 0705 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2303094394 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, March 23 (XINHUA) -- This, China's largest 
economic center is employing advanced auditing methods to 
supervise its rapidly growing economy. 
  According to Deputy Mayor Meng Jianzhu, 84.2 percent of the 
government's financial activities came under the supervision of 
auditing departments last year, in comparison with 71.4 percent 
in 1992. 
  He praised the auditing departments for playing an important 
role in economizing on capital and improving work efficiency in 
urban construction last year. 
  Shanghai is China's leading industrial center with many key 
state enterprises. 
  To help these enterprises to adopt a modern enterprise 
system 
as quickly as possible, the auditing departments audited ten 
joint- stock companies, 82 partnership enterprises and three 
nationwide exchanges of goods and materials last year. 
  The auditing departments also completed checks on 22 items 
of 
loans granted by international banking organizations and put 
forward proposals on making efficient use of the loans to the 
municipal government last year. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

