<F P=101> East Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shanghai Strengthens Air-Traffic Control </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2303120294 Beijing XINHUA in English 1138 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2303120294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shanghai, March 23 (XINHUA) -- An additional air- 
corridor has been opened here to ease the congestion of the 
skies above the China's leading metropolis. 
  Air-traffic control first started in Shanghai in May, 1992, 
with two sectors opened, one extending to the south and the 
other to the north. 
  But the sharp rise in the number of flights has far exceeded 
the ceiling limit in a single regulatory sector, which could be 
a threat to safety. 
  The new fan-shaped control area stretches to the east to 
strike a balance of flight numbers. 

</TEXT>

