<F P=100> HONG KONG &amp; MACAO </F>
<F P=101> Hong Kong </F>
<H3> <TI>   Senior PRC Official Criticizes UK Airport Funding </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK1703053394 Hong Kong SOUTH CHINA MORNING POST in English 
17 Mar 94 p 10 </F>

<F P=103> HK1703053394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong SOUTH CHINA MORNING POST </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By Linda Choy] </F>
  [Excerpt] [Passage omitted] Another senior leader renewed 
attacks on Britain on the airport projects, suggesting that the 
UK was trying to tap money from Hong Kong by building a new 
airport which was "unreasonably expensive." 
  Li Ruihuan, chairman of the Chinese People's Political 
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), told Hong Kong and Macau 
delegates that he could not understand why construction costs 
had been so high, even after taking into account high prices for 
labour and reclamation in Hong Kong. "The construction of the 
airport is to cost U.S.$20 billion (HK$154.38 billion), a price 
so expensive it has never been heard of," said Mr Li, a member 
of the ruling Politburo. "How much of it will be taken away? 
And who will take this money away?" 
  Mr Li asked the people of Hong Kong to shift their focus 
towards the development of the economy, instead of worrying 
about the lack of smooth transition on the political structure. 
[passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

