<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guangdong Community Mediators Help Reduce Crimes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2303091594 Beijing XINHUA in English 0657 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2303091594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, March 23 (XINHUA) -- Mediators from 
Guangzhou's many resident committees have helped patch up over 
9,000 cases of disputes between citizens in the past year, local 
police officials said here recently. 
  Through their mediation, they have prevented 76 crimes or 
suicides, which might have cost 22 lives, the officials said. 
  According to the officials, some 35 percent of these 
disputes 
were related to matrimonial or love affairs, from which quarrels 
easily arise and worsen into crimes. 
  The officials said disputes arising from unreasonable 
behavior in house decorating, noise from home karaoke 
performances and other entertainments also accounted for a large 
share of the mediators' work. 
  While applying traditional morals and laws, the officials 
said, the mediators also used psychological skills in clamping 
down on short-tempered displays by those involved in quarrels. 
  The mediators also helped resident committees organize 
entertainment, sports or mere talks between neighbors to promote 
understanding, harmony and friendship in communities, the 
officials added. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

