<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Guangzhou Reports on 1993 Crime-Fighting Situation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK2403063494 Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE in Chinese 0540 
GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2403063494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guangzhou, 14 Mar (ZHONGGUO TONGXUN SHE)--Last 
year, the Guangzhou City police seized 145.3 kg of heroin and 
over 3.9 kg of "ice" and investigated and punished over 6,500 
people involving in drug trafficking and drug abuse. 
  In reporting to the city people's congress, the Guangzhou 
City Public Security Bureau said that it also seized 1,425 guns 
of various kinds (of which 57 were designed for military use) 
and 3,237 bullets last year. 
  Data has shown that, last year, more than 32,000 people in 
Guangzhou were involved in gambling and were punished, and more 
than 9,700 people were investigated for being involved in 
prostitution, patronizing prostitutes, procuring prostitutes, 
and harboring prostitution. 
  Statistics have indicated that the total value of goods and 
money confiscated by the Guangzhou police in criminal cases 
amounts to more than 310 million yuan. 
  A Guangzhou City Public Security Bureau report says that the 
social order situation in Guangzhou remains quite grim. The 
number of serious criminal cases is increasing steadily, the 
damage resulting from organized crime is increasing day by day, 
and some criminal gangs are becoming underworld societies. 
Manifestations of the "vices in seven aspects" sometimes rise 
and sometimes fall. Road and fire accidents occur frequently. 
  Wang Long, deputy director of the Guangzhou City Public 
Security Bureau has revealed that the number of cases of missing 
cars is increasing day by day, and such cases have become an 
important part of criminal cases in Guangzhou. Last year, 965 
cars and more than 6,600 motor cycles were stolen in Guangzhou. 
  Deputy Bureau Director Wang Long said that, this year, the 
Guangzhou police will make great efforts to improve Guangzhou's 
social order and will curb the momentum in the rising number of 
major and serious cases, will send more policemen to patrol the 
streets, will arm traffic policemen so that they can take care 
of both traffic and social order, and will strengthen the 
management of people from other localities and mobilize the 
residents to set up "small security zones" to promote the 
comprehensive improvement of social order. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

