<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shenzhen Mayor Terms Public Order Situation `Grim' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK2203141894 Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE in English 1328 GMT 
22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> HK2203141894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing ZHONGGUO XINWEN SHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shenzhen, March 22 (CNS) -- Mayor of Shenzhen Mr. 
Li Youwei, speaking today at the sixth meeting of the First 
Municipal People's Congress, said that Shenzhen would take 
positive measures to rectify existing problems. 
  Mayor Li said that the city was still facing some problems 
despite the good results achieved last year. The outstanding 
problem was the grim public order situation with an increase in 
serious criminal cases. The management level over the city was 
not commensurate with the economic development there and this 
resulted in frequent big accidents. There were arduous tasks to 
be done in ensuring safety in the workplace and in protecting 
workers' legal interests and rights. The high inflation rate 
had affected the residents' lives and the industrial structure 
was not reasonable and needed to be adjusted while the pace of 
the transferring of government functions, macro-control and 
administration were not able to meet the demands of development 
of a market economy. All these problems, he added, would be 
solved this year. 

</TEXT>

