<F P=100> Central-South Region </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shenzhen, Zhuhai Apply To Facilitate Entry of Foreigners </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  HK2303151994 Hong Kong WEN WEI PO in Chinese 14 Mar 94 p A16 </F>
<F P=103> HK2303151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong WEN WEI PO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Chinese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By staff reporter team: "Shenzhen and Zhuhai Apply for </F>
State Council's Approval To Exempt Foreign Visitors From 
Obtaining Entry Visas"] 
  [Text] Beijing, 13 Mar (WEN WEI PO) -- Shenzhen and Zhuhai 
have proposed to allow foreigners to enter the territory without 
entry visas provided that the period of their stay does not 
exceed 72 hours. The applications are awaiting approval from 
the State Council. It has been reported that the central 
authorities intend to make an experiment in Shenzhen. 
  Shenzhen's Mayor Li Youwei and Zhuhai's Mayor Liang Guangda 
said today that the two cities had submitted applications to the 
central authorities. Liang Guangda added: It has been learned 
that relevant central ministries and offices, including the 
Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Office for Port Administration, and 
Economic and Trade Office [as published] have been to Shenzhen 
and Zhuhai to conduct on-the-spot study. They are considering 
making an experiment in Shenzhen first and summing up the 
experience some time afterward. 
  Answering a reporter, Li Youwei said: Shenzhen is advancing 
as an international financial city. That is why we made the 
above proposal and are awaiting instructions from the State 
Council. 

</TEXT>

