<H3> <TI>   Shenzhen Begins Three More Construction Projects </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2403073194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0701 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2403073194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Shenzhen, March 24 (XINHUA) -- Ground was broken 
Wednesday [23 March] for three large construction projects in 
the Futian Bonded Zone of this south China boom town 
simultaneously. 
  The largest of the three is the Shenzhen International 
Commercial Center, a cooperative venture between a Canadian 
company and the bonded zone. It consists of two 48-story 
buildings, one 20-story five-star hotel and a host of five-story 
buildings, with a total floor space of some 180,000 sq km. 
  The other two projects are a Hong Kong-funded storage 
building and the 30,000-sq-km Changbao Mansion. 
  According to official sources, the improvement in the 
infrastructure of the bonded zone over the past three years has 
drawn an increasing number of investors. 
  Statistics show that the 19 projects already started in the 
zone involve a total of more than 5.5 billion Hong Kong dollars 
in overseas investment. 
  Over 120 trading companies are ready to start business. 
  The head of the bonded zone said a series of 
foreign-invested 
projects are expected to be launched there this year. 

</TEXT>

