<F P=100> TAIWAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Trade Surplus With U.S. Down From Jan 1994 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2303100294 Taipei CNA in English 0712 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2303100294 </F>
<F P=104>  Taipei CNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [By T.C. Hu] </F>
  [Text] Washington, March 22 (CNA) -- The Republic of China 
[ROC] enjoyed a trade surplus of US$582 million with the United 
States in January 1994, down US$88 million from the same period 
of 1993, according to US Department of Commerce statistics 
released Tuesday [22 March]. 
  During the period, the ROC imported US$1.56 billion worth of 
products from the United States, up US$72 million from December 
1993, white exports were up US$19 million to US$2.14 billion. 

</TEXT>

