<F P=100> Science &amp; Technology </F>
<H3> <TI>   Jiang Zemin Meets Microsoft Chief </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW2303110194 Beijing XINHUA in English 1057 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2303110194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 23 (XINHUA) -- Chinese President 
Jiang Zemin said here today that Microsoft Corporation of the 
United States is welcome to further strengthen mutually 
beneficial relations of cooperation with China. 
  Jiang made the remark at a meeting with President William 
Gates of this leading U.S. software manufacturer. 
  He told the visitor that China attaches importance to the 
development of the information industry. 
  A program is being carried out to build a series of major 
projects to computerize the main economic indexes, Jiang said. 
  Gates said that his three-day visit has helped him know more 
about China, and this is useful for Microsoft to expand its 
cooperation with its Chinese counterpart. 
  Microsoft has a program to increase exchanges with China, 
including training Chinese software personnel, he said. 

</TEXT>

